    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And were continually in the temple,.... At the time of worship, at the hours of prayer, or of public service; and perhaps always privately in an upper room in it, where they, with others, met frequently, and continued, with one accord, in prayer and supplication; See Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 1:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a practice worthy of imitation, whether in the public or private way: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "praising, and blessing God; for his Son Jesus Christ, who had died for their sins, was risen again for their justification, and was now ascended into heaven, to be their advocate there; and for all spiritual bless his Gospel to every creature. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Amen; so let him be praised, and blessed by all the saints, for all that is contained in this Gospel. In a manuscript copy of Beza's, it is added, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"the Gospel according to Saint Luke was published fifteen years after the ascension of Christ;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See Gill on the title of this Gospel \"Lu 1:1\". ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See Gill on the title of this Gospel \"Lu 1:1\". ",
